using Speicher & Brode equations from PSR-1413-3 to compute the 'optimum'
height of burst and associated ground range
uses brents method
reasonablly fast

the nukemap data comes from the javascript code on the nukemap website

tcsh script files 
   runop  overpressures at 1Kt
   rundp  dynamic pressures at 1Kt

you could easily run the codes at different yields or just use the 1Kt data
and cube root scale
